Package: amule
Version: 2.0.1
Revision: 1
Description: All-platform eMule p2p client
License: GPL
Maintainer: ASARI Takashi <asari@sodan.ecc.u-tokyo.ac.jp>

BuildDepends: wxmac, curl-ssl-dev, openssl097-dev, gcc3.3
Depends: macosx, wxmac-shlibs, curl-ssl-shlibs, openssl097-shlibs
GCC: 3.3

Source: mirror:sourceforge:%n/aMule-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 8c4a6cae058ac248bfcb9a57a18fca61
Source2: http://download.berlios.de/amule/aMule-App-Container.tar.bz2
Source2-MD5: 62fdd65957fb125a01051305e4814b6d

SetCC: gcc-3.3
ConfigureParams: --disable-systray --disable-gtk --disable-nls
InstallScript: <<
/usr/bin/install -m 755 -d %i/Applications
cp -R ../amule.app %i/Applications
/usr/bin/install -m 755 src/amule %i/Applications/amule.app/Contents/MacOS/
<<
#DocFiles: COPYING

DescDetail: <<
The "all-platform eMule", it is a eMule-like client for ed2k network,
supporting Linux, *BSD platforms, Solaris, *MacOSX and *Win32 (*soon).
It was forked from xMule project back in september 2003 (not related to
it anymore, except little bits of old code), to drive it to a brand new
direction and quality. Uses wxWidgets (formely known as wxWindows) for
multiplatform support.
<<
Homepage: http://www.amule.org/
